{The Cemetery Warden Mr. Macrae is the cemetery warden in West Kilbride. He says he has never seen a ghost and that he doesn't believe in them. He says that people don't die on a regular basis but he has on average{54 funerals a year. }He visits the cemetery every night to make sure that everything is secure. This helps to deter the vandals who might be tempted to destroy the gravestones.
The{oldest grave}in the cemetery is that of John Simpson and Mary Morris who were buried in 1863.
Although he has been working there for fourteen years, Mr. Macrae has only had one accident: he fell through two coffins when he was burying the third! {
